  "introduction": "The rapid proliferation of social media platforms over the last two decades has fundamentally altered the landscape of adolescent development, creating a complex environment where digital interactions often supersede face-to-face connections. Researchers have observed that the constant stream of curated images and instant feedback loops can significantly distort an individual's self-perception, leading to heightened levels of anxiety and depression among young users. As teenagers strive to engage with vast online communities, they frequently encounter cyberbullying, unrealistic beauty standards, and the pressure to maintain a perfect digital persona, which can erode their mental resilience. The pervasive nature of these technologies means that adolescents are rarely disconnected, resulting in sleep disturbances and reduced attention spans. Consequently, understanding the multifaceted impact of these digital tools is essential for educators, parents, and policymakers who aim to support the psychological well-being of the next generation in an increasingly connected world.",
