    "Psychologically, excessive social media use is linked to increased rates of depression and anxiety, often stemming from social comparison and the fear of missing out on peer activities.",
    "Socially, the rise of online interactions can lead to the erosion of real-world relationships and a decline in empathy, as digital communication lacks the non-verbal cues necessary for deep emotional connection.",
    "Behaviorally, adolescents may exhibit compulsive checking habits and disrupted sleep patterns due to the addictive design of algorithms that prioritize engagement over well-being."
